# Branching Model (authoritative)

See **`docs/ops/git-and-deploy.md`** for the full solo-developer deploy loop.

## Branches

| Branch | Role | Deploys to |
|--------|------|------------|
| **`main`** | Production source of truth | equipqr.app (after Production Release Readiness + `vercel promote`) |
| **`feat/*`, `fix/*`, etc.** | Short-lived work branches | Vercel **Preview**; **`preview.equipqr.app`** aliases latest Preview build |

There is **no git `preview` integration branch** and **no `dev` branch**.

## Rules for agents

1. **Branch off `main`** for new feature, fix, refactor, chore, or experimental work.
2. **All PRs target `main` by default.** Never open PRs into a git branch named `preview`.
3. When GitHub defaults or old docs disagree, **this rule wins**.
4. Before creating a branch:
   ```powershell
   git fetch origin main
   git switch -c feat/<short-name> origin/main
   ```
5. When opening a PR:
   ```powershell
   gh pr create --base main --head feat/<short-name> --title "<conventional-commit title>"
   ```
6. **Pre-production hostname (`preview.equipqr.app`):**
   - Stable Vercel **Preview** URL for your latest work — **not** tied to a git branch named `preview`.
   - Any push to a work branch can update it via `preview-domain-alias.yml`.
   - Supabase **ephemeral PR branches** validate `supabase/**` on PRs to `main`.
   - OAuth (Google Workspace, QuickBooks): verify on the **local stack** before merge.
7. **Hotfix:** Branch off `origin/main`, PR into `main`.
8. **Local E2E before push/PR.** No push and no PR open until `local-verify-before-preview-push.mdc` passes with zero user manual steps.
9. **Worktree tempo:**
   - **Main worktree:** merge via PR to `main` after local verify (protected branch).
   - **Linked worktrees:** full merge-ready workflow per `pr-merge-ready-workflow.mdc`.
   - **Never force-push to `main`.**

See git-powershell.mdc for Windows worktree cleanup gotchas.
